name: Endometriosis Awareness T-shirt | I Wear Yellow For Endometriosis T-Shirt
description:
Help us spread Endometriosis Awareness with this BEE-utiful shirt. 

20% of profits go to the Endometriosis Research Center!

Design: 

"I wear yellow (in yellow) for Endometriosis" with yellow rose and yellow ribbon around rose.

**Vinyl will be accommodating per t-shirt color choice**

 

Customize:

  • Review our "Size Charts" to select the size you need based on the type of t-shirt you would like for this design
  • Review our "Shirt Color Chart" to select the color shirt you would like per the t-shirt type

 

Endometriosis directly affects our Queen Bee Brittany. She is working very hard to spread the awareness of Endometriosis as it has affected her quality of life for many years. Bringing awareness to the world about Endometriosis that affects 1 in 10 women worldwide is a huge passion of hers. Even if you do not have Endometriosis this shirt will help us spread awareness of this debilitating disease.

 

What is Endometriosis?

Endometriosis occurs when the tissue that lines the uterus (endometrium) grow on other pelvic organs, such as the ovaries or fallopian tubes, and in rare cases the lungs and brain. Outside the uterus, endometrial tissue thickens and bleeds, just as the normal endometrium does during the menstrual cycle. Since the tissue is outside of the uterus when it bleeds it has nowhere to go. This causes extreme pain and internal bleeding. It is very hard to be diagnosed with Endometriosis and can only be properly diagnosed microscopically/surgically. There is no cure and very little treatment options that tend to not be effective.

name: LOVE HOPE CURE | Endometriosis Awareness T-Shirt
description:
Help us spread Endometriosis Awareness with this BEE-utiful shirt. 

20% of profits go to the Endometriosis Research Center!

Design: 

LOVE HOPE CURE with Yellow Ribbon in replacement of the "O" in HOPE

**Vinyl will be accommodating per t-shirt color choice**

 

Customize:

  • Review our "Size Charts" to select the size you need based on the type of t-shirt you would like for this design
  • Review our "Shirt Color Chart" to select the color shirt you would like per the t-shirt type

 

Endometriosis directly affects our Queen Bee Brittany. She is working very hard to spread the awareness of Endometriosis as it has affected her quality of life for many years. Bringing awareness to the world about Endometriosis that affects 1 in 10 women worldwide is a huge passion of hers. Even if you do not have Endometriosis this shirt will help us spread awareness of this debilitating disease.

 

What is Endometriosis?

Endometriosis occurs when the tissue that lines the uterus (endometrium) grow on other pelvic organs, such as the ovaries or fallopian tubes, and in rare cases the lungs and brain. Outside the uterus, endometrial tissue thickens and bleeds, just as the normal endometrium does during the menstrual cycle. Since the tissue is outside of the uterus when it bleeds it has nowhere to go. This causes extreme pain and internal bleeding. It is very hard to be diagnosed with Endometriosis and can only be properly diagnosed microscopically/surgically. There is no cure and very little treatment options that tend to not be effective.

name: Warrior Onesie
description:
Do you suffer from Endometriosis or PCOS? This adorable onesie is for your little one to help spread Endo & PCOS awareness. 

20% of profits go to the Endometriosis Research Center!

 

Design:

"My mommy is a warrior(in yellow or teal)"

**Onesie comes in white**

 

Endometriosis directly affects our Queen Bee Brittany. She is working very hard to spread the awareness of Endometriosis as it has affected her quality of life for many years. Bringing awareness to the world about Endometriosis that affects 1 in 10 women worldwide is a huge passion of hers. Even if you do not have Endometriosis this shirt will help us spread awareness of this debilitating disease.

 

What is Endometriosis?

Endometriosis occurs when the tissue that lines the uterus (endometrium) grow on other pelvic organs, such as the ovaries or fallopian tubes, and in rare cases the lungs and brain. Outside the uterus, endometrial tissue thickens and bleeds, just as the normal endometrium does during the menstrual cycle. Since the tissue is outside of the uterus when it bleeds it has nowhere to go. This causes extreme pain and internal bleeding. It is very hard to be diagnosed with Endometriosis and can only be properly diagnosed microscopically/surgically. There is no cure and very little treatment options that tend to not be effective.
